<codeline lineno="8"><highlight class="comment"><sp/>*<sp/>The<sp/>`Regions`<sp/>class,<sp/>implemented<sp/>in<sp/>Cython,<sp/>is<sp/>a<sp/>specialized<sp/>selection<sp/>template<sp/>within<sp/>the<sp/>AnalysisG<sp/>framework,<sp/>designed<sp/>for<sp/>defining<sp/>and<sp/>managing<sp/>various<sp/>analysis<sp/>regions.<sp/>It<sp/>inherits<sp/>from<sp/>the<sp/>generic<sp/>`SelectionTemplate`<sp/>class,<sp/>extending<sp/>its<sp/>functionalities<sp/>to<sp/>incorporate<sp/>features<sp/>and<sp/>structures<sp/>relevant<sp/>to<sp/>region-based<sp/>selections.<sp/>This<sp/>class<sp/>provides<sp/>a<sp/>high-performance<sp/>interface<sp/>to<sp/>an<sp/>underlying<sp/>C++<sp/>regions<sp/>object,<sp/>enabling<sp/>efficient<sp/>categorization<sp/>of<sp/>events<sp/>into<sp/>different<sp/>analysis<sp/>regions.</highlight></codeline>
